This paper discusses techniques and tools for high-performance computing on GPUs, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-categories in computer science. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), which focuses on techniques for parallel computing and distributed systems. Other likely sub-categories include cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), as these areas are all relevant to the development of tools and techniques for GPU computing.
